---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';
import { productJsonLd } from '../../lib/structured-data';

const product = getProductBySlug('sovereignty-assessment-toolkit')!;
const jsonLd = productJsonLd(product, 'https://evoked.dev/products/sovereignty-toolkit');
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Sovereignty Assessment Toolkit"
  description="The 47-point sovereignty assessment is free. The $49 toolkit adds the scoring rubric, domain health map, and action-plan template - what you do with your score, not the questions."
  structuredData={jsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Products", "Evaluation design"]}
    headline="Does your product honor human sovereignty?"
    metaphor={["47 points. 7 domains. 90 minutes."]}
    sub="A structured way to find out."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="Why this exists">
    <p class="lede">
      Most products extract value from people without examining whether they
      should. This toolkit gives you a structured, honest way to evaluate whether
      the technology you build - or the technology you use - treats people as
      sovereign beings or as resources to be mined.
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      It does not require an ethics degree. It requires honesty.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="What the $49 adds">
    <p class="pd-body">
      You can run the whole assessment right now for nothing - all 47 items, the 6 red flags, a subtotal for each of the 7 domains, your overall score, and the band it lands in. That is the <a href="/products/sovereignty-checklist">free checklist</a>, and it stays free. The $49 toolkit does not resell you the questions. It adds four things.
    </p>
    <div class="pd-features">
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Polished rubric</h3>
        <p>Reads the pattern across your domain scores, not just the number - what your result actually says about the product.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Domain health map</h3>
        <p>See at a glance which of the 7 domains are strong and which are quietly failing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Action-plan template</h3>
        <p>Prioritize the gaps, assign owners, set timelines. Turn the assessment into a sprint.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Team license + PDF</h3>
        <p>Run it across your org, not just your own desk - in a clean PDF you can hand to a board, a client, or a procurement reviewer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="The seven domains">
    <div class="pd-pillars">
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">1</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Transparency</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Are we honest about what we're doing and why?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">2</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Autonomy</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Does the product support user goals - or hijack them?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">3</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Invitation</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Are we inviting people in - or trapping them?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">4</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Dignity</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Do we treat people as whole beings - or as conversion targets?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">5</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Silence</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Do we know when to stop talking?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">6</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Data sovereignty</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"Who owns what - and do they know it?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">7</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>AI and voice</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">"If an AI speaks for us, does it honor the people it speaks to?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · IV" heading="Who this is for">
    <div class="pd-audience">
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Product teams</h3>
        <p>Run this on your product before your users run it for you. Surface the gaps between what you intend and what you've built.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Procurement and compliance</h3>
        <p>Evaluate vendor products before adoption. A structured rubric is more useful than a trust-me pitch deck.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Founders</h3>
        <p>Build the assessment into your development process from day one. It's cheaper to honor sovereignty than to retrofit it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · V" heading="Buy the toolkit">
    <p class="lede">
      The assessment is free, two ways: as a free Claude skill, <code>/sovereignty-assess</code>, that runs you through the same 47 items conversationally, and as a free <a href="/products/sovereignty-checklist">printable checklist</a> you can score by hand with nothing leaving your desk. The PDF below is the polished, team-ready version - the scoring rubric, the domain health map, and the action-plan template, for offline use and distribution. Sovereignty is the free part; polish is the paid part.
    </p>
    <div class="pd-purchase">
      <div class="pd-price">$49</div>
      <p class="pd-purchase-lead">PDF download. Use it on as many products as you want.</p>
      <a
        href={product.stripePaymentLink}
        class="pd-buy-cta"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >Buy the Toolkit</a>
      <p class="pd-purchase-fineprint">
        Adds the scoring rubric, domain health map, action plan template, and
        the five principles appendix - plus the 47-point checklist formatted
        for print and team distribution. The checklist itself is always free.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" heading="Go deeper" closing={true}>
    <p class="lede">
      The toolkit gives you the assessment. If you want help acting on the
      results, two doorways from here.
    </p>
    <div class="pd-upsell">
      <a href="/consulting" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Sovereignty Assessment Workshop</h3>
        <p>Half-day guided assessment on your product with your team. I facilitate. You discover. $4,000.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Learn more &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call" class="pd-upsell-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <h3>Discovery call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your results and figure out next steps.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">Schedule &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>
